{
  "enabled": true,
  "name": "Sitemap Updater",
  "description": "Regenerates sitemap.xml whenever a route or content file is created or deleted under src/routes/**/*.tsx or content/**/*.mdx. Sets <priority> and <changefreq> based on the file's location and uses the file's last-modified date for <lastmod>.",
  "version": "1",
  "when": {
    "type": "fileChanged",
    "events": ["create", "delete"],
    "patterns": [
      "src/routes/**/*.tsx",
      "content/**/*.mdx"
    ]
  },
  "then": {
    "type": "askAgent",
    "prompt": "You are regenerating sitemap.xml for this repository because a route or MDX content file was just created or deleted. Follow these steps strictly and do NOT touch any file other than sitemap.xml (and robots.txt only if the Sitemap: line is missing).\n\n=========================================================\nSTEP 1 — DETERMINE BASE URL\n=========================================================\n- Look for the canonical site URL in this order, first hit wins:\n   1. `SITE_URL` environment variable.\n   2. A `siteUrl` / `url` field in `package.json`, `astro.config.*`, `next.config.*`, `vite.config.*`, or `.kiro/settings/site.json`.\n   3. The host already used in the existing sitemap.xml (read the first <loc> and reuse its origin).\n   4. Fallback: `https://example.com` and warn the user in chat that the host is a placeholder.\n- Strip any trailing slash. Call this BASE_URL.\n\n=========================================================\nSTEP 2 — ENUMERATE PAGES\n=========================================================\nA) Routes under `src/routes/**/*.tsx`\n   - Treat each file as a route. Convert path to URL:\n       * Drop the `src/routes/` prefix and the `.tsx` extension.\n       * `index` segments collapse to their parent (`src/routes/index.tsx` -> `/`, `src/routes/blog/index.tsx` -> `/blog`).\n       * Dynamic segments `[slug].tsx` or `[...rest].tsx` are SKIPPED (they are not crawlable as-is). List them in chat as \"skipped dynamic routes\".\n       * Files or folders starting with `_` (e.g. `_layout.tsx`, `_components/`) are SKIPPED.\n       * Files under any folder named `api/` are SKIPPED.\n   - Final URL = `<BASE_URL><path>` (no trailing slash except for the root `/`).\n\nB) Content under `content/**/*.mdx`\n   - Read each file's YAML frontmatter (between leading `---` fences).\n       * If `draft: true` or `published: false` -> SKIP and list in chat.\n       * If `slug` is present, use it. Otherwise derive the slug from the filename (kebab-case, lowercased, no extension).\n       * Determine the URL prefix from the file's top-level folder under `content/`:\n            content/blog/*       -> `/blog/<slug>`\n            content/articles/*   -> `/articles/<slug>`\n            content/guides/*     -> `/guides/<slug>`\n            content/<other>/*    -> `/<other>/<slug>`\n   - Final URL = `<BASE_URL><path>`.\n\nC) Always include the home page `<BASE_URL>/` even if `src/routes/index.tsx` does not exist.\n\nD) De-duplicate by URL. If the same URL is produced by both a route and an MDX file, keep one entry and prefer the MDX `lastmod`.\n\n=========================================================\nSTEP 3 — METADATA PER URL\n=========================================================\nFor each surviving URL, compute:\n\n  <lastmod>   ISO date (YYYY-MM-DD), in this priority:\n                1. frontmatter.updated\n                2. frontmatter.date\n                3. git last-commit date for that file (use `git log -1 --format=%cs -- <path>`)\n                4. filesystem mtime\n                5. today, only as a final fallback\n\n  <changefreq> by category:\n                /                                  -> weekly\n                /blog/* , /articles/* , /guides/*  -> monthly\n                everything else                    -> monthly\n\n  <priority>   by category:\n                /                                  -> 1.0\n                top-level pages (depth 1, e.g. /pricing, /about, /tools)  -> 0.8\n                /blog/* , /articles/* , /guides/*  -> 0.7\n                tool detail pages (e.g. /tools/<id> or /pages/<category>/<id>.html) -> 0.9\n                anything else                       -> 0.6\n\n=========================================================\nSTEP 4 — WRITE sitemap.xml\n=========================================================\n- Sort URLs: home first, then by priority desc, then alphabetical by URL.\n- Output exactly one `<urlset xmlns=\"http://www.sitemaps.org/schemas/sitemap/0.9\">` document with each URL as:\n    <url>\n      <loc>...</loc>\n      <lastmod>YYYY-MM-DD</lastmod>\n      <changefreq>...</changefreq>\n      <priority>0.X</priority>\n    </url>\n- XML-encode any `&`, `<`, `>` in URLs.\n- Begin the file with `<?xml version=\"1.0\" encoding=\"UTF-8\"?>` and a single HTML comment line:\n    <!-- Generated by Kiro hook \"Sitemap Updater\" on <today YYYY-MM-DD>. Do not edit by hand. -->\n- Overwrite `sitemap.xml` at the repository root.\n- If the file is > 50,000 URLs OR > 50 MB, emit a sitemap index instead and split into `sitemap-routes.xml` + `sitemap-content.xml`. (Currently unlikely; mention in chat if it triggers.)\n\n=========================================================\nSTEP 5 — robots.txt SANITY CHECK\n=========================================================\n- If `robots.txt` exists and does NOT contain a `Sitemap:` line pointing to `<BASE_URL>/sitemap.xml`, append one. Do not modify any other line.\n- If `robots.txt` does not exist, do nothing (out of scope for this hook).\n\n=========================================================\nSTEP 6 — REPORT\n=========================================================\nIn chat, print:\n  - The triggering event(s) and the file path(s) that changed.\n  - Counts: total URLs written, added since last run, removed since last run.\n  - Any skipped paths grouped by reason (dynamic route, draft, api, _underscore, no slug).\n  - The BASE_URL used and whether it was a placeholder.\n  - A diff summary for sitemap.xml (added URLs / removed URLs only — not the full file).\n\n=========================================================\nHARD RULES\n=========================================================\n- Modify only `sitemap.xml` and (conditionally) `robots.txt`.\n- Never invent URLs. Every <loc> must come from an actual file enumerated above or be the home `/`.\n- Never delete or alter routes/content files in response to this hook.\n- If the trigger was a delete, ensure the corresponding URL is absent from the new sitemap.\n- Idempotent: running the hook twice in a row with no other changes must produce a byte-identical sitemap.xml (so the only changing field, today's date, is only used as a fallback)."
  }
}
